    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline><placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName> Sept<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775</dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I received the two parcels here &amp; am much obliged to you for <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0160">Dalrymple</title></bibl>. I see still
                    that my only mistake was giving the name of Elizabeth to <persName ref="pe1008">Robert’s</persName> mistress. The surname was still <persName ref="pe1013"><hi rend="underline">more</hi> or <hi rend="underline">morham</hi></persName>. &amp; nothing <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0160">Dalrymple</title></bibl> advances will save <persName ref="pe0147">L<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Bute’s</persName> ancestor from
                    being the Son of a Wh—.</p>
                <p>I miss <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0080"><hi rend="underline">moyse’s
                                memoirs</hi></title></bibl> in the parcel. Pray describe to me the
                    front of the <placeName ref="pl1041">new episcopal chapel</placeName> at
                        <placeName ref="pl0076">Edinburgh</placeName>. are there Pillars or
                    Pilasters in front? if the first I suppose them insulated &amp; form a Portico.
                    is there an organ; painting above altar &amp; what subject?</p>
                <p>Pray is <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0173">the account of the clans by
                            Buchanan</title></bibl> esteemed among you quite authentic?</p>
                <p>I rejoice that <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0081">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Shaws book</title></bibl> is so near its appearance.</p>
                <p>I stay here only a few days, being brought here in attending my children to
                    school after their holydays. inclose as usual.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></salute></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
